Package org.mitre.provenance.dag

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    LineageDAGTraverseFn
    This interface is intended to be used with the traverse function within LineageDAG.
    PathCollection.PathCriteria
    A sort of functional-style interface; implement this interface and pass it as an argument to PathCollection in order to filter a collection of paths down to a matching list.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DAGPath
    A DAGPath is a specific thread running through an existing LineageDAG.
    DAGWatcher
    A DAGWatcher is a class that receives signals about items being added to and removed from graphs.
    FingerPrint
    A FingerPrint is a statistical profile of a LineageDAG that stores basic information about the nature of the information in the DAG.
    LineageDAG
    This object represents a limited lineage DAG view composed of PLUSObjects and PLUSEdges.
    PathCatalog
    A catalog of paths through a DAG.
    PathCollection
    This object holds an entire collection of paths, keyed by their source/destination.
    PathStep
    A single step movement through a LineageDAG.
    TraversalSettings
    Controls the settings that the graph traverser uses to determine what to return in response to a given query.
    ViewedCollection
    A collection of provenance nodes and edges that has the context of all being viewable by a given user.
Author:
DMALLEN This package contains classes relevant to the use and traversal of directed acyclic graphs
